1
00:00:43,544 --> 00:00:45,254
Do you love jjajangmyeon that much?

2
00:00:45,337 --> 00:00:46,672
CHAPTER 36:
WHO THE HELL ARE YOU?

3
00:00:46,756 --> 00:00:48,466
Look at you, stuffing your face.

4
00:00:48,549 --> 00:00:49,592
Is it that good?

5
00:00:55,556 --> 00:00:56,724
Mr. Ga!

6
00:00:57,558 --> 00:00:58,684
Are you okay?

7
00:00:58,768 --> 00:01:00,394
Oh, no. I'm sorry.

8
00:01:00,478 --> 00:01:01,562
Are you okay?

9
00:01:01,645 --> 00:01:02,688
Oh, no.

10
00:01:05,608 --> 00:01:07,860
Who are these heavenly figures?

11
00:01:08,986 --> 00:01:10,863
What leads you to descend from on high

12
00:01:10,946 --> 00:01:12,615
to visit my humble place?

13
00:01:13,199 --> 00:01:14,158
Was it you bastards

14
00:01:15,659 --> 00:01:16,660
who put him in that state?

15
00:01:18,537 --> 00:01:19,705
Oh, no…

16
00:01:19,789 --> 00:01:21,290
This is hilarious.

17
00:01:21,791 --> 00:01:23,501
We've got guests here.

18
00:01:23,584 --> 00:01:25,461
Go get them a welcome drink.

19
00:01:25,544 --> 00:01:28,047
Don't just sit around watching.

20
00:01:28,881 --> 00:01:30,633
-Get some tea.
-Keep an eye on the kids.

21
00:01:31,467 --> 00:01:32,551
We can do that.

22
00:01:34,929 --> 00:01:35,763
You got this.

23
00:01:37,681 --> 00:01:38,724
Are you hurt?

24
00:01:42,019 --> 00:01:44,188
-But…
-Don't worry, he'll be fine.

25
00:01:44,980 --> 00:01:46,649
Is picking on kids…

26
00:01:49,109 --> 00:01:50,319
your idea of fun?

27
00:01:58,494 --> 00:02:01,247
What's with these assholes?

28
00:02:04,083 --> 00:02:05,543
-What on earth?
-Hey.

29
00:02:12,925 --> 00:02:13,884
Hey, kid!

30
00:02:17,888 --> 00:02:19,098
Are you crazy?

31
00:02:20,307 --> 00:02:21,308
Get him!

32
00:02:30,651 --> 00:02:31,652
That's how you do it!

33
00:02:33,320 --> 00:02:34,572
Why, you…

34
00:02:39,451 --> 00:02:40,536
What are you playing at?

35
00:02:43,747 --> 00:02:45,416
Are you okay? I guess you are.

36
00:02:58,053 --> 00:03:00,097
-Come at me.
-Hey.

37
00:03:00,180 --> 00:03:03,183
Look, should a teacher
be behaving this way?

38
00:03:03,267 --> 00:03:04,476
-He has a knife!
-A teacher…

39
00:03:22,620 --> 00:03:24,204
Who the hell

40
00:03:24,955 --> 00:03:26,624
are you, bastard?

41
00:03:27,499 --> 00:03:29,793
Me? I'm a Korean literature teacher.

42
00:03:31,170 --> 00:03:34,006
All right, Korean literature teacher.

43
00:03:54,610 --> 00:03:55,611
No, don't look.

44
00:03:59,114 --> 00:04:00,950
Let's go.

45
00:04:05,037 --> 00:04:07,581
EPISODE 12

46
00:04:08,666 --> 00:04:10,167
How are you going to resolve this?

47
00:04:10,793 --> 00:04:12,461
We'll pretend it never happened.

48
00:04:13,379 --> 00:04:14,630
Apologize to the students.

49
00:04:17,675 --> 00:04:18,676
-I'm sorry.
-I'm sorry.

50
00:04:20,511 --> 00:04:22,346
Are you going to show up again?

51
00:04:22,972 --> 00:04:24,056
-No.
-No.

52
00:04:26,809 --> 00:04:28,227
If I ever see you again,

53
00:04:28,978 --> 00:04:30,813
you're going down for real then.

54
00:04:33,148 --> 00:04:35,567
An esteemed shaman told me

55
00:04:35,651 --> 00:04:37,361
I'd live a long and healthy life.

56
00:04:43,283 --> 00:04:44,576
Goodbye, Mr. Teacher.

57
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:46,161
No, boss.

58
00:04:46,245 --> 00:04:47,329
I mean, boss teacher.

59
00:04:49,331 --> 00:04:50,457
Okay. Let's go.

60
00:04:52,960 --> 00:04:53,961
Let's go.

61
00:05:04,346 --> 00:05:07,766
What the fuck? What's up with that prick?

62
00:05:08,392 --> 00:05:10,436
Didn't he say
he was a Korean literature teacher?

63
00:05:10,519 --> 00:05:12,146
How can a teacher fight like that?

64
00:05:13,147 --> 00:05:15,024
He was being deadly serious

65
00:05:15,649 --> 00:05:18,277
when he said he'd kill us
if he ever saw us again.

66
00:05:20,404 --> 00:05:23,407
The look in his eyes was murderous.

67
00:05:23,991 --> 00:05:25,367
What the heck? Who are they?

68
00:05:25,451 --> 00:05:26,660
What if they kidnapped her?

69
00:05:26,744 --> 00:05:28,370
Ji-a lives at the shelter
and works part-time.

70
00:05:28,454 --> 00:05:29,371
What staff?

71
00:05:29,913 --> 00:05:30,831
Your call cannot be…

72
00:05:30,914 --> 00:05:32,166
Why isn't she answering?

73
00:05:32,249 --> 00:05:33,333
CHAPTER 37:
UNMASKED FOR JUSTICE

74
00:05:33,417 --> 00:05:35,127
Why isn't she even checking?

75
00:06:18,962 --> 00:06:21,673
You scared me to death. I was so worried!

76
00:06:22,466 --> 00:06:24,551
The news about Ji-a alone
was terrifying enough,

77
00:06:24,635 --> 00:06:26,178
and I couldn't get hold of you.

78
00:06:26,261 --> 00:06:30,432
My imagination started to run wild,
thinking you'd gotten caught up in it too.

79
00:06:34,103 --> 00:06:36,522
You weren't answering your phone
or checking your messages.

80
00:06:38,982 --> 00:06:40,943
Nobody had any idea where you'd gone.

81
00:06:41,026 --> 00:06:42,778
Do you know how scared I was?

82
00:06:46,615 --> 00:06:48,325
I have a crush on Mr. Ga.

83
00:06:54,665 --> 00:06:55,791
What?

84
00:06:57,626 --> 00:07:01,338
I should've just told you
I have a crush on him,

85
00:07:02,422 --> 00:07:04,049
but I couldn't do it.

86
00:07:04,967 --> 00:07:08,470
I thought you might not understand
after the way we mocked him,

87
00:07:08,554 --> 00:07:10,472
and I wasn't sure exactly how I felt.

88
00:07:11,306 --> 00:07:12,558
So I was flustered.

89
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:14,434
That's why

90
00:07:15,185 --> 00:07:16,562
I ended up hurting you.

91
00:07:17,729 --> 00:07:18,689
I'm sorry.

92
00:07:24,027 --> 00:07:27,281
I was hurt because it seemed like
you were keeping a secret from me.

93
00:07:28,657 --> 00:07:30,617
I didn't care if you liked Dong-ju too.

94
00:07:31,660 --> 00:07:34,788
But I was sad that you couldn't
bring yourself to tell me.

95
00:07:38,375 --> 00:07:40,919
You always tell me everything.

96
00:07:42,629 --> 00:07:45,632
I was the first person you told
about your constipation.

97
00:07:52,097 --> 00:07:54,474
You're my top priority.
You know that, right?

98
00:08:00,063 --> 00:08:00,898
Hey.

99
00:08:01,690 --> 00:08:05,652
If Dong-ju and I both fall into a lake,
who are you going to save first?

100
00:08:08,322 --> 00:08:10,449
You used to compete in toddler swim meets.

101
00:08:13,869 --> 00:08:14,745
Seriously?

102
00:08:17,664 --> 00:08:19,583
So, did something happen?

103
00:08:23,212 --> 00:08:25,672
Even if I tell you,
you're never gonna believe it.

104
00:08:25,756 --> 00:08:26,882
What?

105
00:08:26,965 --> 00:08:27,966
Come on, tell me.

106
00:08:29,259 --> 00:08:31,678
At first, the gangsters

107
00:08:31,762 --> 00:08:33,639
totally looked down on Mr. Yoon.

108
00:08:34,223 --> 00:08:36,892
Like, "What? Who does he think he is?"

109
00:08:36,975 --> 00:08:37,935
And then?

110
00:08:38,018 --> 00:08:41,730
Then, he addressed them in an icy tone.

111
00:08:41,813 --> 00:08:44,691
Not the soft voice
he normally uses when he talks to us.

112
00:08:44,775 --> 00:08:46,026
Just really serious.

113
00:08:47,819 --> 00:08:49,821
"Is picking on kids your idea of fun?"

114
00:08:49,905 --> 00:08:51,198
He said it just like that.

115
00:08:51,281 --> 00:08:53,700
I got goose bumps just hearing it.

116
00:08:53,784 --> 00:08:58,372
Then, it was just a whirl of front kicks,
back kicks, and flying kicks.

117
00:08:58,455 --> 00:09:00,249
He even grabbed them by the collar

118
00:09:00,332 --> 00:09:02,501
and punched them.

119
00:09:02,584 --> 00:09:04,461
It was just like a movie.

120
00:09:04,544 --> 00:09:05,754
And after that,

121
00:09:06,380 --> 00:09:09,258
his shirt sleeve got torn.

122
00:09:09,341 --> 00:09:10,342
Torn?

123
00:09:10,425 --> 00:09:12,970
He had a huge tattoo.
You know Medusa, right?

124
00:09:13,053 --> 00:09:15,097
He has one here

125
00:09:15,180 --> 00:09:18,475
with several dragon-like creatures

126
00:09:18,558 --> 00:09:20,686
coiling and writhing all over.

127
00:09:20,769 --> 00:09:21,979
It's absolutely huge.

128
00:09:23,272 --> 00:09:24,273
Dong-ju…

129
00:09:26,984 --> 00:09:28,277
has a tattoo?

130
00:09:29,278 --> 00:09:30,112
Yeah.

131
00:09:30,737 --> 00:09:33,615
It was quite faded,
so I guess he's had it for a long time,

132
00:09:34,241 --> 00:09:35,701
but it looked like a Medusa for sure.

133
00:09:37,744 --> 00:09:41,748
It looked like it covered his shoulder
and continued on to his back,

134
00:09:41,832 --> 00:09:43,208
but I didn't actually see his back.

135
00:09:43,792 --> 00:09:44,626
Then,

136
00:09:45,585 --> 00:09:46,712
Dong-ju was…

137
00:09:48,880 --> 00:09:50,340
I think

138
00:09:50,966 --> 00:09:52,509
he used to be a gangster himself.

139
00:10:02,519 --> 00:10:03,770
Are you okay?

140
00:10:07,357 --> 00:10:08,400
Dong-ju

141
00:10:09,318 --> 00:10:10,736
used to be a gangster?

142
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:21,580
Maybe I shouldn't have said anything.

143
00:10:22,622 --> 00:10:23,582
No! Just a moment.

144
00:10:23,665 --> 00:10:24,791
I haven't even touched you.

145
00:10:25,709 --> 00:10:27,169
Hang on a second.

146
00:10:27,252 --> 00:10:28,170
-Ready?
-I…

147
00:10:29,087 --> 00:10:30,380
-Stop moving.
-Do his lips too.

148
00:10:30,464 --> 00:10:31,631
Stay still!

149
00:10:31,715 --> 00:10:33,550
-Stop it. That hurts.
-All done.

150
00:10:34,051 --> 00:10:35,677
-We'll put the Band-Aid on later.
-It hurts.

151
00:10:35,761 --> 00:10:38,221
Jeez, he's going to
give me a breakdown at this rate.

152
00:10:38,305 --> 00:10:39,639
Let's see your hand.

153
00:10:39,723 --> 00:10:42,476
Your hand is a mess.
What are you going to do about it?

154
00:10:43,643 --> 00:10:44,895
At least your left hand is okay.

155
00:10:50,817 --> 00:10:51,818
How are you holding up?

156
00:10:54,404 --> 00:10:55,947
I swore I would never fight again.

157
00:10:59,493 --> 00:11:00,702
But look what happened.

158
00:11:03,538 --> 00:11:05,082
And in front of students too.

159
00:11:06,249 --> 00:11:07,834
It couldn't be helped.

160
00:11:09,294 --> 00:11:11,213
They even saw my tattoo.

161
00:11:14,132 --> 00:11:15,967
What am I going to do now?

162
00:11:29,815 --> 00:11:31,066
Do you remember?

163
00:11:33,693 --> 00:11:35,195
Back when I was in 11th grade,

164
00:11:35,278 --> 00:11:37,614
you got in a motorcycle accident
and passed out.

165
00:11:37,697 --> 00:11:38,865
I dragged you to the hospital,

166
00:11:39,449 --> 00:11:40,575
but as soon as you came to,

167
00:11:40,659 --> 00:11:43,453
you swung your fist at me,
yelling, "Was it you?"

168
00:11:43,537 --> 00:11:44,413
Damn it.

169
00:11:45,580 --> 00:11:47,666
I thought you were the one who hit me.

170
00:11:49,084 --> 00:11:50,794
You even bought me rice porridge.

171
00:11:51,878 --> 00:11:53,171
It was so weird.

172
00:11:53,964 --> 00:11:57,050
I was wondering why you bought it
after I beat you up for no reason.

173
00:11:57,717 --> 00:11:59,010
It was the middle of winter.

174
00:11:59,511 --> 00:12:01,596
And you were only wearing slides.

175
00:12:01,680 --> 00:12:03,515
You looked younger than me,

176
00:12:03,598 --> 00:12:06,017
and I just assumed you were struggling
at your part-time job.

177
00:12:07,811 --> 00:12:10,480
You were the first to be kind to me
without expecting anything in return.

178
00:12:11,773 --> 00:12:12,983
So I felt embarrassed.

179
00:12:15,527 --> 00:12:18,989
I thought if I carried on down that path,
I'd end up doing something really bad.

180
00:12:19,906 --> 00:12:22,242
I wondered if I could become like you.

181
00:12:25,078 --> 00:12:26,621
If I hadn't met you,

182
00:12:27,247 --> 00:12:28,832
I'd still be living that kind of life.

183
00:12:32,878 --> 00:12:33,879
At the time,

184
00:12:35,130 --> 00:12:37,048
I thought you were a freak.

185
00:12:40,218 --> 00:12:41,970
But for some reason,
I felt I'd run into you again.

186
00:12:42,762 --> 00:12:43,638
Why?

187
00:12:43,722 --> 00:12:44,723
I don't know.

188
00:12:46,892 --> 00:12:47,726
No idea.

189
00:12:50,812 --> 00:12:52,314
When I went to our college orientation,

190
00:12:53,106 --> 00:12:55,025
who should I see but this round face?

191
00:12:55,901 --> 00:12:57,611
I was actually quite pleased to see you.

192
00:12:57,694 --> 00:12:58,862
Weren't you?

193
00:13:01,364 --> 00:13:02,199
You know.

194
00:13:02,866 --> 00:13:04,326
This guy looked kind of dumb.

195
00:13:04,409 --> 00:13:05,994
-Screw you.
-I bet he did.

196
00:13:06,077 --> 00:13:08,205
-He still does.
-Whatever, you idiots.

197
00:13:10,749 --> 00:13:13,251
Why distinguish the guy you're now
from the one you were back then?

198
00:13:14,336 --> 00:13:16,129
They're both still you.

199
00:13:18,798 --> 00:13:20,467
You just have to accept it and move on.

200
00:13:24,971 --> 00:13:27,516
But Dong-ju is no ordinary dude.

201
00:13:28,141 --> 00:13:30,685
Setting his mind to studying
and going from a street thug

202
00:13:30,769 --> 00:13:33,146
to an education student at our college
in just two years?

203
00:13:33,230 --> 00:13:34,606
-How is that possible?
-It isn't.

204
00:13:34,689 --> 00:13:35,524
Exactly.

205
00:13:36,107 --> 00:13:37,359
He had it in him all along,

206
00:13:38,318 --> 00:13:40,070
but the circumstances
weren't right for him.

207
00:13:40,987 --> 00:13:43,615
And by the way…

208
00:13:43,698 --> 00:13:46,409
When was the last time
we saw Dong-ju show off his skills?

209
00:13:46,493 --> 00:13:48,119
-When was it?
-At that convenience store.

210
00:13:48,203 --> 00:13:49,246
Right!

211
00:13:50,080 --> 00:13:51,289
It's the first time since then, no?

212
00:13:51,873 --> 00:13:53,416
-Why won't you let it go?
-That store.

213
00:13:53,500 --> 00:13:55,168
We were all complete zombies,

214
00:13:55,252 --> 00:13:58,880
dragging our feet to the convenience store
to pick up some cup ramyeon.

215
00:13:58,964 --> 00:14:02,259
Some thugs were harassing the girl
working at the cash register.

216
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:15,105
Is picking on kids

217
00:14:16,439 --> 00:14:17,399
your idea of fun?

218
00:14:21,027 --> 00:14:23,488
Me? I'm a Korean literature teacher.

219
00:14:28,535 --> 00:14:31,371
I can't believe
Mr. Yoon had a secret like that.

220
00:14:32,247 --> 00:14:34,666
Most of the time,
he hides his real identity.

221
00:14:34,749 --> 00:14:36,376
But when someone needs protecting,

222
00:14:37,210 --> 00:14:38,295
he fights.

223
00:14:41,631 --> 00:14:44,134
Here it comes.
My next wave of inspiration.

224
00:14:46,845 --> 00:14:50,181
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 8

225
00:14:58,189 --> 00:15:00,400
Forget it. Where is that place anyway?

226
00:15:00,483 --> 00:15:02,027
The food there melts in your mouth.

227
00:15:09,159 --> 00:15:10,243
Let's just go.

228
00:15:14,873 --> 00:15:15,874
What do you want?

229
00:15:17,584 --> 00:15:19,961
Didn't anyone ever teach you

230
00:15:20,045 --> 00:15:23,381
that fists are for protecting people,
not harming them?

231
00:15:23,465 --> 00:15:25,675
I guess you're here to teach us, huh?

232
00:15:42,275 --> 00:15:43,568
If I ever see you again,

233
00:15:44,569 --> 00:15:46,154
you're going down for real then.

234
00:15:48,490 --> 00:15:49,866
Let's go.

235
00:15:50,950 --> 00:15:52,285
I could just…

236
00:15:53,328 --> 00:15:54,287
I was going to help you,

237
00:15:54,371 --> 00:15:56,331
but it looked like
you had it all under control.

238
00:16:00,168 --> 00:16:01,670
"If I ever see you again,

239
00:16:02,712 --> 00:16:04,756
you're going down for real then."

240
00:16:08,176 --> 00:16:09,177
So cool.

241
00:16:10,178 --> 00:16:12,722
He's so cool.

242
00:16:16,643 --> 00:16:20,522
CHAPTER 38:
SIR! I HAVE SOMETHING TO SAY!

243
00:16:32,909 --> 00:16:33,743
Hi.

244
00:16:45,547 --> 00:16:46,673
What's up with her?

245
00:16:46,756 --> 00:16:47,674
I don't know.

246
00:16:48,425 --> 00:16:49,384
She's scaring me.

247
00:16:57,267 --> 00:17:00,145
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

248
00:17:00,228 --> 00:17:02,397
-Mr. Ga, your face.
-What happened?

249
00:17:02,480 --> 00:17:03,606
-Are you okay?
-Sir!

250
00:17:03,690 --> 00:17:04,816
Were you in a fight?

251
00:17:04,899 --> 00:17:06,025
Mr. Ga!

252
00:17:06,109 --> 00:17:09,195
-Seriously, who did this to you?
-What happened?

253
00:17:09,279 --> 00:17:11,906
Were you in a fight?
What's wrong with your face?

254
00:17:11,990 --> 00:17:13,533
Sir.

255
00:17:13,616 --> 00:17:14,617
Quiet.

256
00:17:14,701 --> 00:17:15,744
Don't worry, I'm fine.

257
00:17:15,827 --> 00:17:17,245
-My gosh.
-You don't look okay.

258
00:17:17,328 --> 00:17:18,496
We'll start with roll call.

259
00:17:19,789 --> 00:17:21,458
-Jeon Ji-min.
-Here.

260
00:17:21,541 --> 00:17:22,625
-Oh Ji-ho.
-Here.

261
00:17:22,709 --> 00:17:24,043
It's worse than I imagined.

262
00:17:24,127 --> 00:17:25,044
-Kim Ga-yeong.
-Here.

263
00:17:25,128 --> 00:17:26,796
It's better than yesterday.

264
00:17:26,880 --> 00:17:28,173
Hey, you two.

265
00:17:28,757 --> 00:17:30,800
-Hong Su-min.
-I see you've made up.

266
00:17:30,884 --> 00:17:31,760
Jeon Chae-won.

267
00:17:32,594 --> 00:17:33,928
-When did we ever fight?
-Im Su-yeon.

268
00:17:37,348 --> 00:17:39,142
-Lee Eun-ji.
-Here.

269
00:17:39,225 --> 00:17:40,602
-Choi Hye-jeong.
-Here.

270
00:17:42,937 --> 00:17:45,023
Give it your all in class today.
Have a good one.

271
00:17:45,648 --> 00:17:47,525
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

272
00:17:52,864 --> 00:17:53,990
Mr. Ga!

273
00:17:59,996 --> 00:18:02,248
I'm really sorry. It's all my fault.

274
00:18:05,710 --> 00:18:06,628
Are you okay?

275
00:18:08,546 --> 00:18:09,380
Yes.

276
00:18:11,049 --> 00:18:12,926
That's all that matters.
Pay attention in class.

277
00:18:16,846 --> 00:18:17,680
Okay.

278
00:18:35,240 --> 00:18:36,324
Hello.

279
00:18:36,407 --> 00:18:37,325
-Hi.
-Hello.

280
00:18:47,752 --> 00:18:49,128
Are you okay?

281
00:18:50,255 --> 00:18:52,757
I've decided to think things over.

282
00:18:56,135 --> 00:19:00,598
You know, Mr. Yoon
isn't that kind of person anymore.

283
00:19:00,682 --> 00:19:04,227
I think he's a really great guy.

284
00:19:04,978 --> 00:19:07,105
Never mind.
It's not my place to say anything.

285
00:19:07,939 --> 00:19:09,649
If that's how you feel, that's that.

286
00:19:10,650 --> 00:19:13,027
If you've decided you no longer like him,

287
00:19:13,736 --> 00:19:14,696
that's fine.

288
00:19:16,197 --> 00:19:17,907
When did I say that?

289
00:19:20,118 --> 00:19:21,119
Isn't that what you mean?

290
00:19:22,912 --> 00:19:24,581
From now on, I'll be the one.

291
00:19:25,999 --> 00:19:29,127
No matter how fierce the storm gets,
I'll make sure he isn't knocked over

292
00:19:29,210 --> 00:19:30,628
or hurt in any way.

293
00:19:31,254 --> 00:19:32,422
I'll be the one to do it.

294
00:19:34,757 --> 00:19:35,592
Go-ya.

295
00:19:36,342 --> 00:19:38,386
So I need to get into a good college

296
00:19:38,469 --> 00:19:40,179
and make a success of myself,

297
00:19:40,263 --> 00:19:42,765
so that I can be someone
Dong-ju can trust and rely on.

298
00:19:44,350 --> 00:19:46,352
If I want to protect Dong-ju,

299
00:19:46,978 --> 00:19:48,271
I have to be able to do so.

300
00:19:50,273 --> 00:19:51,482
I've decided to take the CSAT.

301
00:19:52,025 --> 00:19:54,777
It'll give me more options
than just taking the practical exam.

302
00:19:57,071 --> 00:19:57,989
Now I finally get

303
00:19:58,990 --> 00:20:00,950
why I've been single my whole life.

304
00:20:01,784 --> 00:20:02,619
Huh?

305
00:20:02,702 --> 00:20:04,746
When I like someone,

306
00:20:05,496 --> 00:20:08,416
I just hope they'll like me as I am.

307
00:20:08,499 --> 00:20:10,627
Even if I don't do anything,

308
00:20:10,710 --> 00:20:13,796
I hope they'll fall for me
and be interested in me.

309
00:20:16,758 --> 00:20:19,844
I've only whined like a baby

310
00:20:20,845 --> 00:20:22,055
and gotten jealous so far.

311
00:20:22,764 --> 00:20:25,099
Now I see I have to become someone worthy.

312
00:20:30,021 --> 00:20:32,273
You're already worthy, my friend.

313
00:20:35,735 --> 00:20:36,569
Okay?

314
00:20:40,031 --> 00:20:41,616
What should I do?

315
00:20:48,414 --> 00:20:49,415
Tell him how you feel.

316
00:20:51,876 --> 00:20:53,419
You said he might be going to the US.

317
00:20:55,004 --> 00:20:56,464
-Tell him?
-Yeah.

318
00:20:58,925 --> 00:21:02,053
How would I go about doing that?

319
00:21:03,888 --> 00:21:05,807
First, look him in the eyes.

320
00:21:05,890 --> 00:21:07,350
For at least three seconds.

321
00:21:07,433 --> 00:21:09,102
To show him how serious you are,

322
00:21:10,269 --> 00:21:11,688
gaze into his eyes tenderly…

323
00:21:13,189 --> 00:21:14,482
and deeply like this.

324
00:21:19,612 --> 00:21:22,407
Hey, how am I supposed to do that?

325
00:21:23,282 --> 00:21:24,784
Do you want to tell him or not?

326
00:21:27,537 --> 00:21:28,705
I do.

327
00:21:28,788 --> 00:21:30,915
Then do as I say.
Look him in the eye for three seconds.

328
00:21:33,751 --> 00:21:35,169
Okay, I'll give it a try.

329
00:21:35,253 --> 00:21:36,754
Look him in the eye for three seconds,

330
00:21:36,838 --> 00:21:37,880
tell him you like him,

331
00:21:37,964 --> 00:21:39,507
and leave it at that.

332
00:21:42,427 --> 00:21:44,512
Even if he's not interested,
when he hears that,

333
00:21:44,595 --> 00:21:46,097
do you know what will happen?

334
00:21:47,598 --> 00:21:48,933
He'll

335
00:21:49,559 --> 00:21:50,685
waver.

336
00:21:51,269 --> 00:21:52,729
-Waver?
-Yeah.

337
00:21:52,812 --> 00:21:54,480
He'll waver. I guarantee it.

338
00:21:54,564 --> 00:21:55,982
That's just how guys are.

339
00:21:57,483 --> 00:22:00,778
With your first snow,
you have to just go for it.

340
00:22:02,030 --> 00:22:04,032
Okay, just go for it.

341
00:22:04,532 --> 00:22:07,452
Instead of waiting and agonizing,
just go for it, okay?

342
00:22:08,202 --> 00:22:11,164
Where's a good place to do it?

343
00:22:11,247 --> 00:22:13,082
You have after-school math later.
Just do it then.

344
00:22:14,292 --> 00:22:15,126
Today?

345
00:22:16,586 --> 00:22:17,545
Today…

346
00:22:19,297 --> 00:22:22,008
MURIM GIRLS' HIGH SCHOOL

347
00:22:22,675 --> 00:22:25,053
The graph of the function
will look like this.

348
00:22:25,803 --> 00:22:27,597
-What should I say?
-If the graph of y equals f(x)

349
00:22:27,680 --> 00:22:30,224
and the line y equals k

350
00:22:30,308 --> 00:22:32,143
-Sir, I…
-intersect at one positive

351
00:22:32,226 --> 00:22:34,604
and two negative x-coordinates,
the real value of k

352
00:22:34,687 --> 00:22:37,857
-will range from negative eight to zero.
-To tell the truth, I…

353
00:22:37,940 --> 00:22:40,651
Once you plot it on a graph,
it's easy to understand, right?

354
00:22:40,735 --> 00:22:42,487
Let's leave it here for today. Great job.

355
00:22:42,570 --> 00:22:43,738
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

356
00:22:43,821 --> 00:22:45,281
What?

357
00:22:45,364 --> 00:22:46,449
Class is over already?

358
00:22:51,370 --> 00:22:54,415
For now,
let's wait for the others to leave.

359
00:23:01,422 --> 00:23:02,298
Aren't you going?

360
00:23:04,300 --> 00:23:06,010
I'm just about to.

361
00:23:06,094 --> 00:23:07,053
Sir!

362
00:23:10,681 --> 00:23:12,433
This is it. It's now or never.

363
00:23:19,315 --> 00:23:20,399
Your glasses.

364
00:23:23,069 --> 00:23:24,570
You've got a new pair.

365
00:23:26,864 --> 00:23:28,950
No, I can't do it.

366
00:23:40,002 --> 00:23:41,462
Let's do it. You got this, Eui-ju!

367
00:23:41,546 --> 00:23:42,630
Mr. Ga…

368
00:23:48,553 --> 00:23:51,931
No, I've got to do it today.
Otherwise, I'll never do it.

369
00:24:03,151 --> 00:24:05,778
Mr. Ga! Wait a minute.

370
00:24:05,862 --> 00:24:07,613
Sir! I have something to say!

371
00:24:07,697 --> 00:24:08,823
Just a moment.

372
00:24:08,906 --> 00:24:10,074
Wait.

373
00:24:10,158 --> 00:24:11,784
Just a second.

374
00:24:15,997 --> 00:24:16,998
Just a moment.

375
00:24:22,962 --> 00:24:24,005
What is it?

376
00:24:41,063 --> 00:24:41,981
I…

377
00:25:06,339 --> 00:25:07,840
Eui-ju, come with me.

378
00:25:07,924 --> 00:25:08,966
Why is he so uptight?

379
00:25:09,050 --> 00:25:10,426
Isn't he just following the rules?

380
00:25:10,509 --> 00:25:12,178
That might actually be more fair.

381
00:25:12,261 --> 00:25:13,930
There's a web novel with main characters

382
00:25:14,013 --> 00:25:16,057
who are exactly like
the Korean literature, Math, PE,

383
00:25:16,140 --> 00:25:18,059
and Japanese teachers from our school.

384
00:25:18,142 --> 00:25:20,102
I'm really curious who wrote it.

385
00:25:20,186 --> 00:25:21,520
You're done for.

386
00:25:21,604 --> 00:25:23,022
I thought you should know, Mr. Ga.

387
00:25:23,105 --> 00:25:24,273
It was Eui-ju.

388
00:25:24,357 --> 00:25:25,191
What do you mean?

389
00:25:25,274 --> 00:25:26,192
Is it really you?

390
00:25:26,275 --> 00:25:27,109
To tell the truth…

391
00:25:27,193 --> 00:25:28,694
-The thing is, Go-ya--
-This is insane.

392
00:25:28,778 --> 00:25:30,279
I'll see that she's expelled.

393
00:25:30,363 --> 00:25:32,281
Just pretend you didn't know.

394
00:25:32,365 --> 00:25:34,367
I don't want you getting in trouble
because of me.

395
00:25:34,450 --> 00:25:37,286
Hello, this is Imuk.

396
00:26:33,592 --> 00:26:35,594
Subtitle: Paul Carver
